-o , --other <string>

Allows some parameters to be changed even though they do not have their
own command line option. The argument to this option is a variable, or a "variable=value"
assignment, with no spaces around the equal sign. The variables that
are recognized are:.

bpf , bpf=l,u -- band pass filter, lower and upper cutoffs optional.
hpf , hpf=n -- high pass filter, lower cutoff frequency n optional.
lpf , lpf=n -- low pass filter, upper cutoff frequency n optional.
sm=x,n,z -- smooth parameters, Time, Drop, and DB.
sq=x,n -- squeeze parameters, DB and Keep.
ek=x -- apply an echo effect, x = delay in milliseconds.
vs=x -- variable speed factor, 0.8 <= x <= 2.0, or a time value.

a time value must have an M separating minutes and seconds, and may have
an H separating hours from minutes.

